------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ENV - Build & RUN time
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ENV is used to define environment variables that are available inside the container at runtime. 
It is mainly used for configuration like ports, URLs, credentials, etc.

ENV APP_PORT=8080
ENV DB_HOST=localhost

echo $APP_PORT

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARG - Build time
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARG is used to pass values during image build time. 
It is not available when the container is running. 
It is mainly used for versions and build configs.

ARG VERSION=1.0
FROM node:$VERSION

docker build --build-arg VERSION=18 -t myapp .

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ARG - RUN time
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USER is used to run the container with non-root privileges for security purposes.

RUN useradd -m appuser
USER appuser
